  "articleSummary": "The article is a tutorial‑style post aimed at developers who maintain personal or small‑scale static sites and are considering a migration from an older Gatsby setup. It argues that Astro is the most pragmatic choice because its simple API, lack of cloud or framework bias, and strong static‑site features let the author meet strict performance and deployment requirements with minimal friction. Key points include a brief requirements checklist, a comparison of Astro’s `.astro` components versus client‑side frameworks, and a rundown of the supporting stack (Tailwind, MDX, Pagefind, Utterances, Netlify). The tone is practical and slightly anecdotal, using the metaphor of “choosing the right tool for the job” and recurring “quickly do meaningful things” framing to highlight Astro’s ease of use.",
